description:
A one-off collection released by Virgin Publishing, reprinting several stories from Doctor Who Magazine, including the titular The Mark of Mandragora, a seventh Doctor sequel to the TV fourth Doctor story The Masque of Mandragora. All stories, originally publushed in black and white, were colourised for this release.

Contents

  1. Train-Flight, from Doctor Who Magazine #159-161
  2. Doctor Conkerer, from Doctor Who Magazine #162
  3. Teenage Kicks, an illustrated prose story from Doctor Who Magazine #163
  4. Fellow Travellers, from Doctor Who Magazine #164-166
  5. The Mark of Mandragora, from Doctor Who Magazine #169-172

The League explores an old CADMUS facility in search of a.w.o.l. member Micron--who may or may not have gone native while investigating Kobra. A larger, darker secret is about to be revealed...and it could spell DOOM for Earth!
name: Embedded

description:
The Fourth Doctor Volume 1

"Enter a dimension where the robot centurians of the mighty Roman Empire travel from planet to planet, crushing all in their path – driven by cruel gods of greed, destruction and despair...

Explore a world where feelings are a crime, where love is punishable by death, and where the Nervous, the Brave and the Half Daft must unite with their ‘Great Emoter’ in a desperate fight for freedom…

Visit an ordinary street in an ordinary town, but one where aliens lurk in the coal shed and the cabbage patch, where good and evil travel in disguise, and where your best hope of escape is the 5A bus...

Travel to a future where the colonists of New Earth are under attack by the vicious Wereloks – but the ferocity of these beasts is as nothing beside the calculated cruelty of their masters...

Discover a realm where a crazed criminal can reshape creation to her will, where the laws of time and space mean nothing, and where a simple request for a cup of tea could lead to the end of everything...

Join the Doctor, that immortal traveller in time and space, on five of his wildest and wittiest comic strip adventures. The Time Lord’s courage and ingenuity is all that stands against evil and oppression – even though he’d happily swap it all for a bag of jelly babies and a week in Benidorm!"

Contents

  1. The Iron Legion, from Doctor Who Weekly #1-8
  2. City of the Damned, from Doctor Who Weekly #9-16
  3. The Star Beast, from Doctor Who Weekly #19-26
  4. The Dogs of Doom, from Doctor Who Weekly #27-34
  5. The Time Witch, from Doctor Who Weekly #35-38

Timeslip, which was originally published in Doctor Who Weekly #17-18, and so should have gone between the third and fourth stories here, was left out, and subsequently reprinted in third volume of this graphic novel series, The Tides of Time. As of Timeslip, and hence as of The Star Beast in this collection, the Doctor's television companion K-9 began appearing in the comic strip; the Doctor's other TV companion, Romana, is merely noted as being absent, suggesting these stories are set between TV episodes while Romana was taking a sabbatical from travelling with the Doctor. The Star Beast also introduced Sharon Davies, who became the first comic strip companion created by Doctor Who Magazine writers, and the first black companion in the series' history. A teenager, Sharon was aged to adulthood at the end of The Time Witch. The Star Beast himself, the villainous Beep the Meep, would return to menace the Doctor in no less than four later comic strips, plus an audio play. Sharon's school friend, "Fudge" Higgins, would also return in one of these stories, Star Beast II, in Doctor Who Yearbook 1996.
name: The Iron Legion

description: Evening's Empire had begun as a black and white comic strip intended for Doctor Who Magazine, but only the first part had been published, in Doctor Who Magazine #180, before deadline problems arose. By the time these were resolved, the comic strip slot for Doctor Who Magazine was filled by other stories, so the decision was made to publish it as a colour one-off special, under the Doctor Who Classic Comics banner which was normally used for reprinting older Doctor Who strips from early issues of Doctor Who Magazine, TV Comic, Countdown, TV Action and the Doctor Who Annuals.
name: Evening's Empire

description:
Wolverine leads X-Force into their deadliest mission yet: kill Apocalypse, or die trying! But what they find splits the team apart and sets them against each other!

By Rick Remender and Jerome Openal.

Also: Deadpool encounters Steve Rogers and his Secret Avengers, and gets a job offer! But supervillain psychiatrist Doctor Bong plans to destroy them all!

By Daniel Way and Carlo Barben.

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Force #3-4, and Deadpool #28.

The Avengers face the end of all human life on earth as Luke Cage is possessed by a mystical threat! Iron Fist confronts Dr Strange!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Stuart Immonen.

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #2-4.

The Annihilus Swarm threatens to overrun the world – unless a lone hero can stop them! The Fantastic Four face the worst day of their lives in the shocking conclusion of ‘Three’! Guest-starring the greatest heroes of the Marvel Universe!

Includes material reprinted from Fantastic Four #587-588.

Who Was Ben Reilly? Concludes! Peter Parker’s past collides with his future! Can Peter Parker save his family and himself?!!

Plus, Deadpool-Man, Deadpool-Man – does whatever a Deadpool can…spins a web any size – but not really…Deadpool’s don’t have webs. Look out! Here comes the Deadpool-Man! What force on Earth could possibly induce Webheaded Wonder and the Merc with a Mouth to team-up?!! More importantly, will Spidey’s sanity survive the encounter?!

Also, classic adventure as Spider-Man finds himself caught between Blacklash, the Scorpion and the Rhino!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #610-611 and Amazing Spider-Man #319.

Norman Osborn has saved the best for last as he takes on the most personal item on his evil To-Do list. The violent tension between Spider-Man and Norman has grown for years and has been building to a boil for the last few months after Osborn’s last defeat at Spidey’s hands at the end of America Son. Norman can no longer put off what needs to be done.

Plus, They’re Hunting Spiders…The Gauntlet an incredible new Spier-saga begins here! The event that redefines Spider-Man's classic arch-enemies one by one starts with one of his deadliest – Electro! Destitute and desperate, conned out of his life's meaning and worth—Max Dillon becomes the voice of the common man against the brutal injustice of a system overloaded by greed. With Spider-Man already looking over his shoulder. Brace yourselves for a story of a hero with everything to lose against a man with nothing left to gain. Prepare for death’s short, sharp shock. Prepare for Electro.

Plus, one-half benevolent philanthropist/one-half underworld mastermind, Mr. Negative has carved out a substantial slice of the big apple for himself over the past year. But when the super-villain mastermind The Hood strikes at the heart of Mr. Negative’s criminal operations with a whole horde of classic Arachno-Foes (including The Scorcher, Speed Demon, The Squid and the long awaited return of the White Rabbit), Spider-Man is left to clean up the mess between these two violent nemeses!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Reign: The List Amazing Spider-Man, Amazing Spider-Man #612 and Dark Reign: Mr Negative #1!

His electric abilities waning and waxing uncontrollably while the power of his fame grows, Electro turns to an unexpected ally to seek a cure for his condition!

Plus, Spidey and Mayor Jameson have to put their differences aside to pull the plug on the supercharged Electro once and for all, but at the cost of one of the best-known and most beloved landmarks in the Marvel Universe!

Plus, the streets of Chinatown run red with blood as The Hood sends in his entire villain army to take out the last villain standing who refuses to submit to his rule, Mister Negative! The only thing that can save him is the latest ruthlessly violent enforcer he's converted to his cause: the Amazing Spider-Man! Wha-huh? Plus: as Betty Brant gets ever closer to uncovering the terrifying secret behind Mr. Negative's origin, is she unwittingly sealing her own doom?

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #613-614 and Dark Reign: Mr Negative #2.

A locked room mystery! A string of brutal murders! A missing girl! One of Peter Parker's closest friends on the brink of ruin! This looks like a job for the Amazing Spider-Sleuth... and all clues point to the sinister Sandman! But all of Spidey's classic villains are being reinvented as part of The Gauntlet, and the Sandman is no different!

Also, With The Hood and Mr Negative locked in a battle to the death, Betty Brant is poised to unlock the secret origin of the Chinatown's lord of crime, and to stop her he has sent his newest corrupted enforcer to end her life – Peter Parker, the Lacerating Spider-Man!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #615-616 and Dark Reign: Mr Negative #3.

‘The Gauntlet’ continues to close around Spider-Man in this heartbreaking story of love, loss and lust for power, as a NEW Rhino charges into Spider-Man's life, out to make a name for himself... by killing the Rhino!

Also, Spider-Man joins forces with the Fantastic Four and Thor to defend New York from the inter-dimensional might of Dominus!

Plus, classic action as the Assassination Nation Plot begins! Spider-Man has a deadly encounter with the hired gun Paladin! But is there more to this battle than meets the eye?!!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #617, Amazing Spider-Man #320 and How To Break Into Comics The Marvel Way #1.

‘The Gauntlet’ continues to close around Spider-Man in this heartbreaking story of love, loss and lust for power, as a NEW Rhino charges into Spider-Man's life, out to make a name for himself... by killing the Rhino!

Also, Spider-Man joins forces with the Fantastic Four and Thor to defend New York from the inter-dimensional might of Dominus!

Plus, classic action as the Assassination Nation Plot begins! Spider-Man has a deadly encounter with the hired gun Paladin! But is there more to this battle than meets the eye?!!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #618-619, Amazing Spider-Man #321.

Mysterio’s made his big move and a criminal empire is his for the taking! Or is that just more sleight of hand? More mobsters! More mayhem! More magic tricks! And a fight to the finish with Mr. Negative versus Spider-Man versus Mysterio! The big question is: What prize goes to the winner?

Also, Spidey needs a favour from the Black Cat. Nothing big. He just needs her help stealing one of Mr. Negative most valuable possessions. It's not like anything could go oh-so-horribly wrong! Also in this issue: a dark turn for Carlie Cooper, a disturbing development for Curt Connors, and a malicious move by... Aunt May!?!

Plus, classic adventure as the Assassination Nation Plot continues! Spider-Man side-by-side with the beautiful but deadly Silver Sable, as they try to uncover a plot to kill the king Symkaria!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #620-621 and Amazing Spider-Man #322.

While the war for Asgard rages there’s always time for a grudge match or two. Cue Spider-Man versus Venom! ‘Nuff said!

Also, As the Gauntlet rages on around him, the spotlight is on Peter Parker’s original archenemy-turned-best friend, Flash Thompson. Since losing his legs in service to his country, Flash Thompson’s not been deterred by his physical limitations. But even a hero can have his limits. Plus, Spider-Man comes face-to-face with Morbius, The Living Vampire!

Plus, classic action, as the Assassination Nation Plot continues! With the C.I.A. implicated in the urder of Symkaria’s prime minister and the king’s fiancée it’s down to Spider-Man and Captain America to hunt down the real killers!

Includes material reprinted from Siege: Spider-Man, Amazing Spider-Man #622 ,Amazing Spider-Man #323 and Web of Spider-Man Vol.2 #4.
